messages.content:
She narrows her eyes the slightest amount. "...Joseph Biden." She speaks quietly, so to make her words inaudible to anyone but the man they're directed at. "I would be lying if I said I was entirely informed here, however I believe I know everything that matters. I was there to witness the incident myself — the son of an important Arctican man was suddenly murdered by one that sprang from a realm he created."

"There really is no other person I can say this to: the world you lead is a mistake. When I was first introduced to you, all I knew about you was that you were the leader of an important nation in your world, elected by the people. As such, when I coincidentally met a group of dissenters collected outside your palace, I thought it odd. How could a sentiment against a leader specifically contorted to the will of the citizens allow it to reach such a point? That's why I saw fit to give you the benefit of the doubt, and I defended you. A leader's absence in the public eye has many explanations, after all. I have learned just now that it's because you were busy murdering one of our own."

"It is true that Dextrum was in my house unduly. I still do not know what he was doing there. At this point, though, it isn't my priority. The fact of the matter is that the most important person in this simulated reality abandoned his people to wreak havoc in a world inherently beyond his."

"I hope you can see how this is frustrating to me. I can only guess how informed you are as to the nature of this project at this project at this point, so I'll fill you in: a power vacuum exists in the royal family. Not in the sense you'd expect, however. A man went behind the back of the crown, and effectively ripped it to the side of the highest echelon; he granted himself and another man power, one that doesn't occupy the same the same space as the crown while still being absolutely immense. Now, that space is eating itself alive."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
"One of the heads of The Antarctica Project is no longer in communication with the man who created the PDAs. Funny enough, said engineer is the other head of the Project. The logical progression is obvious; there has been an unexpected conflict between parties who vie over control of a rift in reality that transports failed heads of state to directly murder our people."

"Obviously, neither of these people are fit for the position they've assigned themselves — not in their current state, at least. In situations like this, I believe it's the role of a level-headed third party to take the reins. I do not want to cause undue chaos by telling Aodh or Zita directly; additionally, they are significantly less informed than I. Therefore, I'm leaving the role to myself. My emotional stakes are minimal; while I have participated in the project and enjoyed my time with it, there is nobody on Earth I care strongly about. This makes me the best person in existence for the job of filling the power vacuum and ending The Antarctica Project."

"Perhaps the destruction of Earth is an unnecessary step to take in the completion of this goal. I still do not entirely understand how the rift between worlds works. However, I have no guarantee another won't spontaneously open itself; it is a bit of a drastic measure, considering how much sunk time Virtos believed to be worth investing in it, so I will look into every possibility once I have usurped control. The hardest part will be learning the mechanics without an ally explaining them to me... though I suppose I'm rambling now."

"That is all. Consider me telling you this like a message in a bottle, lost to the ocean. I'm... lacking in personal connections I can trust with this at the moment. Enjoy the rest of your stay here."

Of course, the question of "Why am I here" is an explicitly open one. I could answer just as easily that I came here because I wanted to. It was my intention, I can confirm, to come and meet the Baby Crippler, however, the exact actions that I intended to take here aren't for the most certain. I-"

He checks the note in his pocket.

"...I intend to, er- I intend to enact the...

I simply wanted to talk with-"
